{"id": 8027, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "4-2-covalent-bonding", "title": "20N.1.HL.TZ0.9", "topic_id": "4", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Which of these species contains the shortest carbon to oxygen bond length?</span></p>\n<p>A.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>−</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>OH</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi>COO</mi><mo>−</mo></msup></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mi>COOH</mi></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>More than 60% of the candidates identified the compound with the shortest C to O bond as ethanoic acid, with the most common incorrect answer being the ethanoate ion.</p>\n</div>"}